<HEADLINE>
FT  28 NOV 94 / International Company News: Philippines mine lower
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By JOSE GALANG
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   MANILA
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
Benguet, the Philippines' leading mining company, reported net profits for
the nine months to end-September of 13.8m pesos (Dollars 0.58m), a steep
drop of 95.7 per cent from the previous year. Total operating revenues
amounted to 2.24bn pesos, down 6.3 per cent.
The results were affected by poor ore grade which 'significantly improved'
by the start of the fourth quarter of the year. The company expects full
recovery by the first half of 1995.
Gold production, Benguet's principal activity, suffered a decline following
an earthquake that damaged part of the Antamok mine, with the clean-up later
delayed by heavy rains. Losses from its Antamok open-pit mine in the January
to September period reached 42.1m pesos, down, however, from the previous
year's 70.3m pesos.
Copper production, on the other hand, slowed in the third quarter due to
breakdowns in the Dizon mine's concentrator plant.
