</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Eclipse Blinds has sold the business and assets of the Apollo Blinds retail
franchise to Hunter Douglas (UK) for Pounds 2.4m cash, plus an estimated
Pounds 190,000 in respect of the value of certain debtors attributable to
the Apollo business.
Apollo makes window blinds for franchise retail outlets in the UK and Irish
Republic and supplies about 70 outlets which sell window blinds under the
Apollo brand name.
The sale is in line with Eclipse's policy to develop around the profitable
merchandised distribution of textiles and the component parts of window
blinds.
