FT  28 NOV 94 / Observer: Legend has it
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Anyone who knows anything about Greek mythology will find Bill Rooney's
choice of come-back vehicle a trifle bizarre. Little more than a year after
he was forced off the board of Spring Ram by institutional investors upset
by three profit warnings in eight months, Rooney has taken control of
Atreus, a bathroom goods supplier. According to Greek legend the House of
Atreus was cursed and the story of his family 'is virtually unrivalled in
antiquity for complexity and corruption', according to the Encyclopedia
Britannia.
At one point Atreus serves Thyestes, his elder brother, the flesh of
Thyestes' own son, whom Atreus had earlier slain. Welcome back Bill.
