<TEXT>
CRICKET: Australia v England, November 25-29, 1st Test, Brisbane.
Australia's curious decision not to enforced the follow-on, after skittling
England out for a paltry 167, means that the 1st Test - and England's agony
 -spills into this week. Spinner Phil Tufnell rediscovered the art of
serious wicket-taking on the third day, but it looks like being a long, hard
winter for England supporters.
GOLF: Sun City Million Dollar Challenge, December 1-4, Sun City,
Bophuthatswana.
The course, designed by Gary Player, is spectacular and the prize money
staggering. Twelve of the world's top golfers compete for Dollars 1m. On his
home ground, US Open winner Ernie Els will be favourite with local fans and
the bookies.
CHESS: World Olympiad, December 1-13, Moscow.
The battle between Garry Kasparov and Anatoly Karpov over who runs Russian
chess means their side is likely to be missing Karpov's talents on Thursday,
when the 120-nation biennial contest starts. Private banker Duncan Lawrie
sponsors a Nigel Short-lead England team, which hopes to improve on the
three silver medals and the bronze England have won in the past decade.
