FT  28 NOV 94 / Business Travel: BT in the air
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Britain's BT has announced an air-borne fax and data service for airlines
and business jets that is said to operate at twice the speed of existing
facilities. Initially the service will be available across an area from the
Pacific to the Persian Gulf, via satellite consortium Skyphone.
The service will become global when software is installed shortly at ground
earth stations in Singapore and Norway. BT said: 'The lack of a faster fax
and data facilitiy has held some (airline) operators back from (installing)
on-board passenger communications.'
