<HEADLINE>
FT  28 NOV 94 / Business Travel: Literary snapshot
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
A galaxy of writers, including seven Nobel laureates, published a literary
snapshot of the world last week with diaries of a day plucked at random:
April 29 1994. The French magazine Le Nouvel Observateur compiled accounts
by 240 writers and called them A Day in the World. Colombia's Gabriel Garcia
Marquez says he was woken on April 29 by a telephone call to his hotel room
and a woman's voice saying: 'Felipe expects you for dinner at eight.' A
frequent traveller, the writer checked his location by consulting the sign
he had posted by his bedside the night before: 'I am in Madrid.' His dinner
host was Spanish prime minister Felipe Gonzalez.
