FT  28 NOV 94 / Tesco protest at Sainsbury action
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Tesco, the supermarket chain, has protested to its rival J. Sainsbury over
the order to remove a Tesco 20-page Christmas advertising supplement,
containing Pounds 7.50 worth of vouchers, from copies of the Radio Times on
sale in Sainsbury stores.
Sainsbury sent out the order by computer but soon withdrew it. It said it
had been 'an error of judgment'.
