<HEADLINE>
FT  28 NOV 94 / Customs 'may lose 4,000 officers'
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By ROBERT TAYLOR
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
More than 4,000 Customs and Excise jobs will be lost as a result of
tomorrow's Budget, the CPSA civil service union said yesterday, Robert
Taylor writes.
In particular, it predicted that public spending cuts would lead to a loss
of up to 600 jobs among Customs officers patrolling the coastline, ports and
airports.
Mr Geoff Lewtas, the union's national officer for Customs, said that such
cuts would make it more difficult to stop the import of drugs in bulk. He
said: 'These job cuts will do serious damage.'
