<HEADLINE>
FT  26 NOV 94 / World Commodities Prices: Spices
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Spices Pepper prices were under pressure in western Europe because of the
absence of buyers in the US, reports Man Producten. India reported a firmer
local market, however. In the cloves market demand from India and Singapore
encouraged exporters from Madagascar to increase prices. The Madgasacar
crop, now in full swing, is expected to be smaller, largely as a result of
last year's tornado. Nutmegs and mace prices remained generally stable.
