<HEADLINE>
FT  26 NOV 94 / Sainsbury in rethink after 'error' over Tesco
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By RICHARD PULLIN
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
The J. Sainsbury supermarket chain is to review its policy on the sale of
magazines containing advertising coupons for competitors after it was
disclosed that store managers were mistakenly asked to remove a Tesco
supplement from the Radio Times.
The 20-page supplement contained cut-out coupons offering savings on a range
of Christmas items.
Sainsbury said that its head office had electronically messaged its 353
stores yesterday with an instruction to take out the supplement, but a
second message had been sent an hour later cancelling the order.
It added: 'The instruction to remove the advertising insert from the Radio
Times was an error of judgment. It was speedily rectified.'
Sainsbury did not know how many stores had acted on the instruction or how
many copies of the magazine were affected.
Tesco said it was 'very surprised' at hearing about its rival's action, but
it would not take the matter any further.
