<HEADLINE>
FT  26 NOV 94 / Weekend Money (Financial Planning): Top annuity rates
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By PETER QUINTON, Annuity Bureau
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
Despite Generali increasing its annuity rates by 1.5%, the downward trend
has continued, writes Peter Quinton of the Annuity Bureau. Canada Life moved
its annuity rates down by 0.8% on November 21, and, on November 22, three
other life companies, London Life, Prudential and Abbey Life chose to reduce
their rates by 1.1%, 1% and 0.08%, respectively. The downward trend is in
part due to actuaries responding to a reduction in gilt yields.
An annuity provides a guaranteed income for life in return for a lump sum
investment. The bulk of the fund built up by many types of pension plan must
be used in this way. This week's table shows COMPULSORY PURCHASE ANNUITY
RATES which are used for small company schemes and additional voluntary
contribution plans (AVCs) and freestanding AVCs (FSAVCs) among others. This
week's rates include inflation proofing.
 -----------------------------------------------------------------------
Escalating at 5% pa               Escalating at 5% pa
Male age 55    Annuity (0%*)      Female age 50   Annuity (+2.1%*)
 -----------------------------------------------------------------------
RNPFN        Pounds 6,591.96      Sun Life         Pounds 5,411.64
Generali     Pounds 6,563.22      Prudential       Pounds 5,302.56
Sun Life     Pounds 6,532.68      Generali         Pounds 5,288.52
 -----------------------------------------------------------------------
Escalating at 5% pa               Escalating at 5% pa
Male age 60    Annuity (0%*)      Female age 60      Annuity (0%*)
 -----------------------------------------------------------------------
RNPFN        Pounds 7,663.44      RNPFN            Pounds 6,643.20
Generali     Pounds 7,490.68      Royal Life       Pounds 6,566.35
Royal Life   Pounds 7,449.21      Sun Life         Pounds 6,522.36
 -----------------------------------------------------------------------
Escalating at 3% pa               Escalating at 3% pa
Male age 70    Annuity (0%*)      Female age 70      Annuity (0%*)
 -----------------------------------------------------------------------
RNPFN       Pounds 12,691.92      RNPFN           Pounds 10,707.84
Royal Life  Pounds 12,048.07      Royal Life      Pounds 10,357.83
Sun Life    Pounds 11.883.00      Generali        Pounds 10,213.64
 -----------------------------------------------------------------------
JOINT LIFE - 100% SPOUSE'S BENEFIT
Escalating at 5% pa               Escalating at 5% pa
Male age 60                       Male age 65
Female age 57  Annuity (+2.4%*)   Female age 63   Annuity (+0.1%*)
 -----------------------------------------------------------------------
Sun Life        Pounds 5,702.88   Generali         Pounds 6,438.85
Generali        Pounds 5,697.44   RNPFN            Pounds 6,435.48
Royal Life      Pounds 5,609.77   Royal Life       Pounds 6,421.53
 -----------------------------------------------------------------------
*Month's movement
Payments are monthly in arrears, without a guarantee period. Rates are
at 22 November1994. Figures assume an annuity purchase price of Pounds
100,000 after paying and are shown gross. RNPFN annuities are available
only to nurses and allied workers.
